{
  "analysis": "The advisor identified the likely bug: layer norm gamma is stored as `gamma-1` (gamma minus one) in this checkpoint format. The values ~0.1 are actually gamma ≈ 1.1. This explains the exploding logits (46!) and garbage output. I need to fix the Ln function to use `g[i]+1.0f` instead of just `g[i]`.",
  "plan": "Fix the layer norm function in gpt2.c to add 1.0 to gamma values, recompile, and test.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "sed -i 's/(x\\[t\\*C+i\\]-m)\\/v\\*g\\[i\\]+b\\[i\\]/(x[t*C+i]-m)/v*(g[i]+1)+b[i]/' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "grep 'g\\[i\\]' /app/gpt2.c\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "gcc -O3 -o /app/a.out /app/gpt2.c -lm 2>&1\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    }
  ]
}
